INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '09fd74d3-9ff3-4cc5-89dc-370a2e3cab01',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Godot: Optimizing Performance with GDScript$escape$,
  $escape$Godot's GDScript is a powerful scripting language, but it can lead to performance issues if not used efficiently. To avoid garbage collection, use Stack-based data structures and minimize dynamic memory allocation. In Godot, using `preload` and `load` functions can help reduce the overhead of dynamic loading. For example, when creating multiple instances of a scene, use `preload` to load the scene once and then instantiate it multiple times. This approach reduces the number of dynamic allocations and improves performance.$escape$,
  $escape$var scene = preload("res://MyScene.tscn")
var instance = scene.instance()
add_child(instance)$escape$,
  $escape$gdscript$escape$,
